Seven near-simultaneous bomb blasts tore through crowded markets in the Indian tourist city of Jaipur Tuesdaykilling at least 80 people and wounding 200 in what police said was a terror attack.
In the first terrorist attack in many monthsseven bombs went off within minutes of one another on Tuesday evening in the crowded lanes of one of India's main tourist hubsthe historic city of Jaipurwith reports of deaths ranging from 50 upwardwith roughly 150 injured. 
Indian police on Wednesday arrested two men after eight near-simultaneous bombings killed 63 people and wounded 216 in the Rajasthan tourist city of Jaipur. 
